HEADWORD: Latterly
<hw>Lat"ter*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Lately; of late; recently; at
a later, as distinguished from a former, period.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Latterly</qex> Milton was short and thick.</q>
<rj><qau>Richardson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lattermath</ent>⟦br⟧
